A Pound of Butter - Honesty

There was a farmer who sold a pound of butter to a baker. One day the baker decided to weigh the butter to see if he was getting the right amount, which he wasnâ€™t. Angry about this, he took the farmer to court.

The judge asked the farmer if he was using any measure to weight the butter. The farmer replied, â€œHonor, I am primitive. I donâ€™t have a proper measure, but I do have a scale.â€ The judge asked, â€œThen how do you weigh the butter?â€ The farmer replied; â€œYOUR HONOR, LONG BEFORE THE BAKER STARTED BUYING BUTTER FROM ME, I HAVE BEEN BUYING A POUND LOAF OF BREAD FROM HIM. EVERY DAY WHEN THE BAKER BRINGS THE BREAD, I PUT IT ON THE SCALE AND GIVE HIM THE SAME WEIGHT IN BUTTER. IF ANYONE IS TO BE BLAMED, IT IS THE BAKER.â€ Moral of the story: In life, you get what you give. Donâ€™t try and cheat others.
